class Solution {
public:
    int leastOpsExpressTarget(int x, int target) {
        if (target == 1) return 0;
        if (target == x) return 1;
        int res = 1e9;
        for (int i = 1; i * i <= target; i++) {
            int left = target - i * i;
            if (left % x == 0) {
                res = min(res, 2 + (left / x == 1 ? 0 : 1) + (i == 1 ? 0 : 2));
            } else {
                int j = left / x + 1;
                res = min(res, 2 + (j - 1) * 2 + (left % x > 0 ? 1 : 0));
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(target))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We use a brute force approach to find the least number of operators. We iterate from 1 to sqrt(target) and for each i, we calculate the remaining value left. If left is divisible by x, we update the result with the minimum of the current result and 2 + (left/x == 1 ? 0 : 1) + (i == 1 ? 0 : 2). If left is not divisible by x, we update the result with the minimum of the current result and 2 + (j-1)*2 + (left%x > 0 ? 1 : 0), where j is the largest integer such that j*x <= left.

